Brazilian Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  is concerned the international crisis may freeze credit
as it did in 2008, Guilherme Barros, a columnist at Sao Paulo-
based news website IG  said , without saying how he obtained the
information.  Mantega sees signs that the Chinese economy is slowing and
has moved up his return to  Brazil  from the U.S., Barros said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
